column1: Table 1: Cumulative Number of Cases Tested Positive for COVID-19 - as reported on that date on SG website
(asterisk * denotes less than 5, for disclosure reasons).

column18: *** on 19 July 2020, a result from Fife was revised resulting in a decrease of 1 in the number of positive cases from 937 to 936. ***

*** on 24 July 2020, NHS Forth Valley de-notified one previous case so their number decreased by 1. NHS Lothian had two new cases, but also de-notified one previous case, giving them a net gain of 1 new case. ***
*** on 7 August 2020, NHS Grampian, NHS Greater Glasgow & Clyde and NHS Lothian each de-notified one previous case - their numbers represent the net gain. ***
*** One positive case that was assigned to NHS Grampian on 8 Auguust 2020 has been reassigned to NHS Shetland as they are a resident of NHS Shetland and had been tested while visiting Grampian ***
*** on 10 August 2020, NHS Forth Valley de-notified four previous cases - their numbers represent the net change (negative). ***
*** One positive case in NHS Lanarkshire was de-notified - their numbers represent a net gain of zero but one new case was reported on 13 August 2020.***
